      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is truly heartbreaking to feel that your worth was contingent on external validation and success. When the pedestal crumbles, it can feel like you vanish entirely, leaving only the painful residue of what was. However, the core of who you are exists independent of titles, prestige, or other people's perceptions. You deserve to be seen for the resilient, complex person underneath the collapse, and that intrinsic worth doesn't depend on any external measure.",
      "source": "target",
